							(“the 2003 Regulations”) for such a student;except where paragraph (c) applies, in the case of a student residing at his parent's home, the amount specified in paragraph 3 thereof;in the case of a student receiving an allowance or bursary under the Education (Scotland) Act 1980 , the amount of money specified as  “standard maintenance allowance” for the relevant year appropriate for the student set out in the Student Support in Scotland Guide issued by the Student Awards Agency for Scotland , or its nearest equivalent in the case of a bursary provided by a college of further education or a local education authority...;in any other case, the amount specified in paragraph 2(2) of Schedule 2 to the 2000 Regulations other than in sub-paragraph (a) or (b) thereof;
	- “student” means a person, other than a person in receipt of a training allowance, who is attending or undertaking— a course of study at an educational establishment; ora qualifying course;
	- “student loan” means a loan towards a student's maintenance pursuant to any regulations made under section 22 of the Teaching and Higher Education Act 1998  , section 73 of the Education (Scotland) Act 1980 or Article 3 of the Education (Student Support)

